accessibility.text: P1: it's not a person in…what people don’t realize…it is not a person in a suit. you are meeting the actual character.
P3: i’m very good at still sort of ignoring [reality] apparently.

P5: [social relations] you can feel, you can touch, you can kiss, you can caress you, can interact with, you can fight with even, so, there is a fine but definite line between fictional characters and [social relations].
P7: you just allow yourself to be to be self to be swept up in it, so to speak. i certainly do anyway.
